cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with denoising of medical images using deep learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on retinal optical coherence tomography images in ophthalmology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a deep convolutional autoencoder and a priorly trained ResNet image classifier as regularizer indicates that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the paper deals with medical images suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of regularized autoencoders suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
